' @anti-pattern
' @instead Use DEFINE once, then SET to update
' @description Using DEFINE twice with the same name instead of SET

' DEFINE creates a new name. Using it again with the same name
' is a preparation error. To change an existing value — use SET.

DEFINE counter
0
END

' This is a preparation error:
DEFINE counter
1
END

' Correct approach:
'
' DEFINE counter
' 0
' END
'
' SET $counter
' 1
' END

EXIT
